+## Shared Validation Note
+
+Both public Fibonacci strategies should rely on the same validation helper before any calculation begins.
+
+- Accept integer-like inputs that provide `__index__`.
+- Reject `bool`, strings, floats, and other non-integer-like values with `TypeError`.
+- Reject negative integer-like values with `ValueError`.
+- Normalize accepted inputs to the built-in `int` so both strategies receive the same type.
+- Keep this logic in a small shared validation module, not inside the recursive step logic or iterative loop.
+- Future strategies should call the same helper first so accepted inputs, exception types, and messages stay consistent.
+
